abstract: President Donald Trump signed an executive order on Friday aimed at preventing counterfeit products from abroad from being sold to U.S. citizens who shop online using Amazon.com, Walmart.com or other ecommerce websites, the White House said.
snippet: President Donald Trump signed an executive order on Friday aimed at preventing counterfeit products from abroad from being sold to U.S. citizens who shop online using Amazon.com, Walmart.com or other ecommerce websites, the White House said.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Donald Trump signed an executive order on Friday aimed at preventing counterfeit products from abroad from being sold to U.S. citizens who shop online using Amazon.com, Walmart.com or other ecommerce websites, the White House said.
headline_main: Trump Signs Executive Order Aimed at Preventing Sales of Counterfeit Goods From Overseas
headline_print_headline: Trump Signs Executive Order Aimed at Preventing Sales of Counterfeit Goods From Overseas

abstract: A Connecticut opera singer charged with using an SUV to blast through barricades outside of President Donald Trump's Florida estate, drawing law enforcement gunfire, refused to appear in court Saturday, delaying her initial appearance.
snippet: A Connecticut opera singer charged with using an SUV to blast through barricades outside of President Donald Trump's Florida estate, drawing law enforcement gunfire, refused to appear in court Saturday, delaying her initial appearance.
lead_paragraph: WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. — A Connecticut opera singer charged with using an SUV to blast through barricades outside of President Donald Trump's Florida estate, drawing law enforcement gunfire, refused to appear in court Saturday, delaying her initial appearance.
headline_main: Woman Charged in Mar-a-Lago Chase Refuses to Appear in Court
headline_print_headline: Woman Charged in Mar-a-Lago Chase Refuses to Appear in Court

abstract: The turbulence of impeachment, a contentious presidential campaign and a global virus health threat confront President Donald Trump as he prepares to deliver his State of the Union address Tuesday night. But one thing about the Trump era has remained remarkably steady: public opinion on the president.
snippet: The turbulence of impeachment, a contentious presidential campaign and a global virus health threat confront President Donald Trump as he prepares to deliver his State of the Union address Tuesday night. But one thing about the Trump era has remai...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The turbulence of impeachment, a contentious presidential campaign and a global virus health threat confront President Donald Trump as he prepares to deliver his State of the Union address Tuesday night. But one thing about the Trump era has remained remarkably steady: public opinion on the president.
headline_main: Polling: Americans Dissatisfied With the State of the Union
headline_print_headline: Polling: Americans Dissatisfied With the State of the Union

abstract: A future U.S.-UK trade agreement must incorporate strong provisions on worker rights, environmental protection, and enforcement to ensure bipartisan support, U.S. House Ways and Means Committee Chairman Richard Neal said on Friday, staking out a claim for Congress to help shape any such accord.
snippet: A future U.S.-UK trade agreement must incorporate strong provisions on worker rights, environmental protection, and enforcement to ensure bipartisan support, U.S. House Ways and Means Committee Chairman Richard Neal said on Friday, staking out a c...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A future U.S.-UK trade agreement must incorporate strong provisions on worker rights, environmental protection, and enforcement to ensure bipartisan support, U.S. House Ways and Means Committee Chairman Richard Neal said on Friday, staking out a claim for Congress to help shape any such accord.
headline_main: U.S.-UK Trade Deal Needs Labour, Climate Protections, Enforcement-U.S. Lawmaker
headline_print_headline: U.S.-UK Trade Deal Needs Labour, Climate Protections, Enforcement-U.S. Lawmaker

abstract: Less than a month after being sworn in as Georgia's new U.S. senator, Republican Kelly Loeffler faces a 2020 election battle that's already shaping up to be so contentious that odds are it won't be over until 2021.
snippet: Less than a month after being sworn in as Georgia's new U.S. senator, Republican Kelly Loeffler faces a 2020 election battle that's already shaping up to be so contentious that odds are it won't be over until 2021.
lead_paragraph: ATLANTA — Less than a month after being sworn in as Georgia's new U.S. senator, Republican Kelly Loeffler faces a 2020 election battle that's already shaping up to be so contentious that odds are it won't be over until 2021.
headline_main: Crowded Senate Battle in Georgia Likely Won't End Until 2021
headline_print_headline: Crowded Senate Battle in Georgia Likely Won't End Until 2021

abstract: With the Senate voting to bar any new witness testimony, the only outstanding question is when President Trump will be acquitted.
snippet: With the Senate voting to bar any new witness testimony, the only outstanding question is when President Trump will be acquitted.
lead_paragraph: Senator Lamar Alexander really knows how to drain the suspense from an impeachment fight, doesn’t he?

abstract: Palestinian President Mahmoud Abbas threatened Saturday to cut security ties with both Israel and the U.S. in a speech at an Arab League meeting in which he denounced the White House plan for ending the Israeli-Palestinian conflict.
